WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:00:35.536 --> 00:00:36.744
[people shouting]

3
00:00:43.252 --> 00:00:46.170
[Palmer] You're all in violation
of your Helios contract!

4
00:00:46.755 --> 00:00:50.216
Every penny lost will be docked
from your pay.

5
00:00:50.216 --> 00:00:53.886
- It is right here in black and white.
- That is such bullshit. Palmer.

6
00:00:53.887 --> 00:00:56.139
Helios is a nonunion shop.

7
00:00:57.057 --> 00:00:59.892
Any strike is grounds
for immediate termination.

8
00:00:59.893 --> 00:01:04.563
Then fire us. See how easy it is to do
literally anything up here without us.

9
00:01:04.564 --> 00:01:05.772
[Ed] Fair is fair.

10
00:01:05.774 --> 00:01:08.400
These guys put their asses on the line
every single day.

11
00:01:08.402 --> 00:01:10.403
- That's rich coming from you. Ed.
- They deserve...

12
00:01:10.403 --> 00:01:14.239
I can still hear you whining about how
most of these people aren't even qualified

13
00:01:14.240 --> 00:01:15.659
to be up here in the first place.

14
00:01:16.409 --> 00:01:20.287
But now you're all what?
Down with the common man?

15
00:01:20.289 --> 00:01:22.789
Don't try to make this about me. Dani.

16
00:01:22.790 --> 00:01:26.835
You know as well as I do that Helios.
NASA. Roscosmos

17
00:01:26.837 --> 00:01:28.212
and all the other M-7 countries.

18
00:01:28.212 --> 00:01:30.673
they don't give two shits
about these workers.

19
00:01:30.674 --> 00:01:33.968
Commander Poole.
we are the ones who transformed this base

20
00:01:33.968 --> 00:01:36.762
from a couple of habs
into a viable mining colony.

21
00:01:36.763 --> 00:01:39.640
And all we are asking
is for you to honor the deal.

22
00:01:39.640 --> 00:01:43.477
If we let that rock go to Earth's orbit.
most of our jobs are gone within a year.

23
00:01:43.478 --> 00:01:44.561
[workers murmuring]

24
00:01:44.563 --> 00:01:48.399
What if Helios offered you some kind of...
[stammers] ...guaranteed retraining?

25
00:01:48.400 --> 00:01:49.859
- [murmuring continues]
- Right?

26
00:01:49.859 --> 00:01:52.235
- More education. an opportunity for you...
- [scoffs]

27
00:01:52.236 --> 00:01:53.820
Forgive us. Forgive us.

28
00:01:53.822 --> 00:01:56.115
We've heard that one before.
It's never anything but bullshit.

29
00:01:56.115 --> 00:01:58.950
Listen. if you want your cryo center
to start making the fuel

30
00:01:58.951 --> 00:02:00.368
you need to launch for Goldilocks.

31
00:02:00.370 --> 00:02:02.579
if you want your cargo to get unloaded
from <i>Phoenix</i>.

32
00:02:02.581 --> 00:02:05.707
if you want your habitation units to be
constructed or your food prepared. we...

33
00:02:05.709 --> 00:02:10.463
I have gone out of my way
to address your concerns.

34
00:02:11.131 --> 00:02:14.634
Yes. there is some uncertainty
about the future.

35
00:02:15.218 --> 00:02:19.848
Yes. this asteroid is forcing us
to do things quick. fast and in a hurry.

36
00:02:20.431 --> 00:02:23.644
But we have got to restart
that cryo center ASAP.

37
00:02:24.645 --> 00:02:28.647
We need to pump 125 tons of liquid argon

38
00:02:28.649 --> 00:02:32.151
to get <i>Ranger</i> out to Goldilocks
and push her onto the right path.

39
00:02:32.151 --> 00:02:34.237
And so far. we've only got 44 tons.

40
00:02:34.820 --> 00:02:36.112
We are running out of time.

41
00:02:36.114 --> 00:02:37.781
And every day you keep dragging your feet

42
00:02:37.783 --> 00:02:40.492
is another day closer
to letting Goldilocks get away for good.

43
00:02:40.493 --> 00:02:41.995
And then we all lose.

44
00:02:42.996 --> 00:02:43.997
Is that what you want?

45
00:02:44.581 --> 00:02:45.872
No. what we want is...

46
00:02:45.873 --> 00:02:48.668
We want for you to get off
your goddamn throne

47
00:02:48.668 --> 00:02:50.253
and give us what's fair.

48
00:02:53.465 --> 00:02:55.925
Just how far are you willing
to take this. Ed?

49
00:02:55.925 --> 00:02:58.427
The question is
how much are you willing to lose?

50
00:02:59.179 --> 00:03:01.181
[people murmuring]

51
00:04:18.841 --> 00:04:21.677
These strikers are as driven
as any I've seen.

52
00:04:21.677 --> 00:04:23.387
And I've seen my share.

53
00:04:23.387 --> 00:04:27.057
<i>We cannot allow the progress we made
in Leningrad to go to waste</i>

54
00:04:27.059 --> 00:04:29.976
<i>because of this... this tantrum.</i>

55
00:04:29.978 --> 00:04:32.189
You're preaching to the choir. Irina.

56
00:04:32.689 --> 00:04:36.360
I got the president asking every hour
if this damn thing's been resolved yet.

57
00:04:37.528 --> 00:04:40.612
Korzhenko is the same.
We must bring this to resolution.

58
00:04:40.613 --> 00:04:44.451
<i>Well. they're not budging.
especially on their biggest demand.</i>

59
00:04:45.034 --> 00:04:49.120
This insane idea that they want Goldilocks
to wind up in Mars orbit.

60
00:04:49.122 --> 00:04:51.415
which is non-negotiable for us.

61
00:04:51.415 --> 00:04:53.042
<i>And for us.</i>

62
00:04:53.043 --> 00:04:55.670
There's only one way I see forward.

63
00:04:56.797 --> 00:04:58.005
We go around them.

64
00:04:59.048 --> 00:05:04.762
Order our cosmonauts. your astronauts to
restart the fuel generators immediately.

65
00:05:04.762 --> 00:05:07.180
Well. they're not exactly trained
on that equipment.

66
00:05:07.182 --> 00:05:10.393
<i>They're engineers. This is the only way.</i>

67
00:05:10.394 --> 00:05:12.312
If Helios will not help us.

68
00:05:13.980 --> 00:05:15.565
we'll have to help ourselves.

69
00:05:16.358 --> 00:05:19.235
You said they'd cave in a couple of sols.

70
00:05:19.235 --> 00:05:21.696
- And it's been a week.
- Shut up. you pussy.

71
00:05:21.697 --> 00:05:24.490
You thought this would be easy?
Gotta hold our ground. man.

72
00:05:24.490 --> 00:05:27.242
He's right.
Our power is in sticking together.

73
00:05:27.244 --> 00:05:29.411
They start peeling us off.
this whole thing crumbles.

74
00:05:29.413 --> 00:05:31.329
Look. I came up here to earn.

75
00:05:31.331 --> 00:05:34.125
And all I know is right now.
I'm not earning nothing.

76
00:05:34.125 --> 00:05:36.918
Yeah. well. neither are they.
And they're starting to panic.

77
00:05:36.920 --> 00:05:38.004
[workers murmuring]

78
00:05:38.004 --> 00:05:40.630
- We have to hold the course here.
- [Sam] Right. You gotta be strong.

79
00:05:40.632 --> 00:05:43.425
[worker 1] You heard what Palmer said.
They're gonna shitcan all of us.

80
00:05:43.427 --> 00:05:45.095
[worker 2] They can't. There's no time.

81
00:05:46.305 --> 00:05:50.432
Listen up. I just heard they're gonna try
to start the fuel gennies themselves.

82
00:05:50.433 --> 00:05:52.685
[workers clamoring]

83
00:05:52.685 --> 00:05:55.396
Yeah. they're trying to fuck us.
Are we gonna let that happen?

84
00:05:55.396 --> 00:05:57.816
- [worker 3] Hell no!
- [workers] No! No!

85
00:06:13.790 --> 00:06:15.041
Where are all the suits?

86
00:06:19.379 --> 00:06:21.757
Guys. look at this.

87
00:06:37.021 --> 00:06:40.233
[Danielle] So you're telling me
there are no other accessible suits

88
00:06:40.233 --> 00:06:41.399
on this entire base?

89
00:06:41.401 --> 00:06:45.112
Yes. ma'am. And they used the rovers
to block the air locks at the fuel plant.

90
00:06:45.112 --> 00:06:46.906
It's a clever move.
You gotta give it to 'em.

91
00:06:48.199 --> 00:06:49.449
[Danielle scoffs]

92
00:06:49.451 --> 00:06:51.744
We gotta get creative. Right?

93
00:06:51.745 --> 00:06:53.370
How are we gonna solve this?

94
00:06:53.372 --> 00:06:55.747
We have to get back over
to that cryo center

95
00:06:55.749 --> 00:06:58.959
or we're not gonna have enough fuel
when it comes time to get Goldilocks.

96
00:06:58.961 --> 00:07:02.547
It's just too far a distance
for any sort of improvised pressure suit.

97
00:07:02.548 --> 00:07:05.257
And it's gonna take too long
to make a new one from scratch.

98
00:07:05.259 --> 00:07:06.341
[Danielle] Just stop.

99
00:07:06.343 --> 00:07:08.636
Here we are on the cusp
of grabbing something

100
00:07:08.637 --> 00:07:10.680
that could change everything
for a lot of people.

101
00:07:10.680 --> 00:07:13.766
and we just can't get out
of our own goddamn way.

102
00:07:16.103 --> 00:07:20.524
All right. Well.
what if we went under instead of over?

103
00:07:25.362 --> 00:07:27.947
[grunting. panting]

104
00:07:31.451 --> 00:07:32.827
Oh!

105
00:07:33.536 --> 00:07:34.663
Smells nice.

106
00:07:35.372 --> 00:07:38.081
That'd be the gray water
from the composting tanks.

107
00:07:38.082 --> 00:07:39.625
[grunts]

108
00:07:40.543 --> 00:07:44.423
Well. it's a little tight.
but I think it can work.

109
00:07:44.923 --> 00:07:46.382
You sure they don't know about this?

110
00:07:46.382 --> 00:07:47.841
Uh. it wouldn't even occur to them

111
00:07:47.843 --> 00:07:50.177
that we'd drain the water feed pipe
to the cryo center

112
00:07:50.178 --> 00:07:52.430
and then belly crawl people over there.

113
00:07:52.430 --> 00:07:55.308
[Palmer] But it's gonna take at least
12 hours to fully drain it.

114
00:07:55.850 --> 00:07:57.853
[Danielle] Well.
then we better get started.

115
00:07:59.687 --> 00:08:03.358
ROSCOSMOS

116
00:08:17.372 --> 00:08:19.124
[in Russian] Good morning. Miss Madison.

117
00:08:19.707 --> 00:08:21.043
Good morning. Pasha.

118
00:08:26.380 --> 00:08:27.964
[Irina] <i>We are working with the Americans</i>

119
00:08:27.966 --> 00:08:30.634
to resolve the issues
with the transgressing workers.

120
00:08:30.636 --> 00:08:32.927
[executive]
I would not trust the Americans.

121
00:08:32.928 --> 00:08:36.014
Helios pretends to be
an international company

122
00:08:36.014 --> 00:08:38.682
but it is based in Houston.
right next to NASA.

123
00:08:38.683 --> 00:08:41.729
They serve the interests of Gore
and his lackeys.

124
00:08:41.730 --> 00:08:44.274
[laughs]

125
00:08:46.025 --> 00:08:47.318
What is so funny?

126
00:08:49.238 --> 00:08:54.115
I have met Dev Ayesa and I promise you

127
00:08:54.116 --> 00:09:00.999
he cares more about his own interests
than America's.

128
00:09:01.667 --> 00:09:04.626
Margo is right.
Our intelligence conveys the same.

129
00:09:04.628 --> 00:09:07.879
Now. while the strike is brought
to a close.

130
00:09:07.880 --> 00:09:13.219
all efforts must continue to ensure
the safe capture of this asteroid

131
00:09:13.220 --> 00:09:15.221
and its return to Earth's orbit

132
00:09:15.221 --> 00:09:18.517
under Margo Madison's direction.

133
00:09:19.268 --> 00:09:22.104
Thank you. Director Morozova.
[clears throat]

134
00:09:23.230 --> 00:09:29.235
We have updated
2003LC's projected trajectory.

135
00:09:29.235 --> 00:09:35.908
and Tatyana has now calculated
the optimal intercept for <i>Ranger</i>.

136
00:09:36.576 --> 00:09:40.037
She's done some brilliant work.

137
00:09:40.038 --> 00:09:41.874
[Irina] Very good.

138
00:09:42.832 --> 00:09:44.500
That will be all.

139
00:09:44.500 --> 00:09:46.544
The meeting is adjourned.
Everyone is dismissed.

140
00:09:48.838 --> 00:09:52.134
Margo Madison... stay behind. please.

141
00:10:06.315 --> 00:10:07.316
[door closes]

142
00:10:10.777 --> 00:10:12.903
[in English] The strike will end
one way or another.

143
00:10:12.904 --> 00:10:17.408
And we have reached the point
where interfacing directly and in person

144
00:10:17.408 --> 00:10:20.328
with the American capture team
is necessary.

145
00:10:21.746 --> 00:10:27.375
A representative of Roscosmos must go
to Houston to finalize the negotiations.

146
00:10:27.376 --> 00:10:31.213
I agree. And I'll do everything I can
to help prepare them for the trip. So...

147
00:10:31.215 --> 00:10:35.719
President Korzhenko has requested
for you to do this.

148
00:10:37.929 --> 00:10:39.222
Uh. I'm sorry?

149
00:10:40.057 --> 00:10:44.684
We have negotiated diplomatic immunity
for you for entire time you're there.

150
00:10:44.686 --> 00:10:47.355
They cannot touch you.
They cannot arrest you.

151
00:10:47.355 --> 00:10:49.731
I don't... [stammers] No. no.

152
00:10:49.732 --> 00:10:52.903
I... I can't go back.
That was not part of our agreement.

153
00:10:54.196 --> 00:10:55.697
The agreement has changed.

154
00:10:59.534 --> 00:11:05.456
It is imperative to the president that
we send our most capable representative.

155
00:11:06.375 --> 00:11:07.500
Oh. come on.

156
00:11:08.043 --> 00:11:10.043
The only reason Korzhenko
wants me to go back

157
00:11:10.044 --> 00:11:12.421
is so he can stick a finger in Gore's eye.

158
00:11:12.422 --> 00:11:13.506
Perhaps.

159
00:11:14.423 --> 00:11:20.013
But still it would be wise
to accept the request.

160
00:11:29.480 --> 00:11:32.900
[Chase] Uh. now. we're gonna do
a deep dive on this. This stuff with...

161
00:11:33.527 --> 00:11:35.486
Do I need to say 2003LC?

162
00:11:36.321 --> 00:11:37.904
Let's just go with Goldilocks.

163
00:11:37.905 --> 00:11:40.157
Very interested to hear your POV.

164
00:11:40.158 --> 00:11:43.119
and honestly. just what you were thinking
when you saw her.

165
00:11:43.120 --> 00:11:44.245
Uh. saw who?

166
00:11:44.245 --> 00:11:45.413
- Moscow Margo.
- [bell rings]

167
00:11:45.413 --> 00:11:48.374
Back from commercial in ten. nine. eight...

168
00:11:48.375 --> 00:11:50.375
I'm not here to talk about Margo Madison.

169
00:11:50.376 --> 00:11:52.461
- ...six. five...
- You'll be great.

170
00:11:52.461 --> 00:11:54.505
...four. three...

171
00:11:56.008 --> 00:11:57.426
[mouthing] ...one. and...

172
00:11:58.759 --> 00:12:01.721
Good evening.
Welcome to <i>America Now</i>. I'm Zoey Chase.

173
00:12:01.721 --> 00:12:05.640
Later tonight. a car bomb explodes
at the Kingdom Center tower in Riyadh

174
00:12:05.642 --> 00:12:09.352
as the civil war in Saudi Arabia continues
to rage.

175
00:12:09.354 --> 00:12:14.066
<i>But first. joining me now in
an exclusive interview is Aleida Rosales</i>

176
00:12:14.067 --> 00:12:18.528
<i>from Helios Aerospace who worked
side by side with Margo Madison.</i>

177
00:12:18.529 --> 00:12:20.655
<i>the woman majority leader Feinstein
has called</i>

178
00:12:20.657 --> 00:12:23.618
<i>the worst traitor in American history.</i>

179
00:12:23.619 --> 00:12:25.120
<i>Aleida. welcome.</i>

180
00:12:28.081 --> 00:12:29.749
[clears throat] <i>Thank you. Zoey.</i>

181
00:12:29.750 --> 00:12:33.001
<i>Uh. I look forward to discussing
the asteroid 2003LC and...</i>

182
00:12:33.003 --> 00:12:35.962
<i>We'll get to that. First.
tell me about Margo Madison.</i>

183
00:12:35.963 --> 00:12:40.759
<i>For so long she'd been listed amongst the
dead of the Johnson Space Center bombing.</i>

184
00:12:40.760 --> 00:12:42.595
<i>Did you know that she was alive?</i>

185
00:12:42.596 --> 00:12:44.429
[stammering] <i>No. of-of course not.</i>

186
00:12:44.431 --> 00:12:47.807
She fucking sandbagged me.
Barely even asked me about the asteroid.

187
00:12:47.808 --> 00:12:49.393
[Aleida]
<i>Seven other people were never found.</i>

188
00:12:49.394 --> 00:12:51.144
<i>Do you think they're hiding in Russia too?</i>

189
00:12:51.145 --> 00:12:53.813
<i>And how are you feeling
about her proposed return to Houston?</i>

190
00:12:53.815 --> 00:12:54.899
<i>I'm sorry?</i>

191
00:12:54.899 --> 00:12:56.775
<i>Our source
at the State Department is saying</i>

192
00:12:56.777 --> 00:12:58.945
<i>she'll be granted diplomatic immunity
while here.</i>

193
00:12:58.946 --> 00:13:02.908
<i>I thought...</i> [clears throat] <i>...I thought she
wouldn't be allowed back into the country.</i>

194
00:13:03.491 --> 00:13:07.245
[Chase] <i>No one did.
But you came up under her at NASA.</i>

195
00:13:07.245 --> 00:13:09.413
<i>Her defection couldn't have come
out of nowhere.</i>

196
00:13:10.039 --> 00:13:11.039
<i>I mean. I had...</i>

197
00:13:11.041 --> 00:13:14.836
<i>Did you have a sense that she was working
for the Soviets behind the scenes?</i>

198
00:13:14.836 --> 00:13:17.797
<i>You know what I get a sense of? That
you're a...</i> [bleep] <i>...hack of a reporter.</i>

199
00:13:17.798 --> 00:13:20.131
- Okay. Give me that.
- <i>You're...</i> [bleep]...not doing this. okay...

200
00:13:20.133 --> 00:13:21.216
[TV switches off]

201
00:13:21.217 --> 00:13:22.634
Mom. I...

202
00:13:22.635 --> 00:13:24.679
- It was just starting to get good.
- [Aleida sighs]

203
00:13:27.724 --> 00:13:29.017
[Victor sighs]

204
00:13:31.227 --> 00:13:32.227
How you doing?

205
00:13:32.229 --> 00:13:33.312
[Aleida] I'm fine.

206
00:13:36.649 --> 00:13:37.985
The interview wasn't that bad.

207
00:13:39.653 --> 00:13:41.863
In fact. my brother texted me
saying how much he loved it

208
00:13:41.864 --> 00:13:44.283
when you flipped her off
as you were leaving. [laughs]

209
00:13:44.866 --> 00:13:46.576
- I did?
- Yeah.

210
00:13:47.369 --> 00:13:50.037
I mean. he said it was all fuzzed out.
but. uh...

211
00:13:50.038 --> 00:13:51.123
[Victor chuckles]

212
00:13:51.664 --> 00:13:52.665
[Aleida sighs]

213
00:13:53.250 --> 00:13:55.543
This will all blow over in no time.

214
00:13:56.128 --> 00:13:58.337
I don't care about the interview. Vic.

215
00:13:59.338 --> 00:14:01.424
It's her. Margo.

216
00:14:04.552 --> 00:14:05.846
When I first saw her...

217
00:14:08.389 --> 00:14:11.518
I was so happy she was alive. You know?

218
00:14:12.727 --> 00:14:14.062
I couldn't believe it.

219
00:14:15.688 --> 00:14:19.359
But now that she's coming back. I just...

220
00:14:21.278 --> 00:14:22.821
I wish she was still dead...

221
00:14:25.157 --> 00:14:26.158
but she's not.

222
00:14:27.658 --> 00:14:28.911
She's coming back.

223
00:14:30.328 --> 00:14:31.871
She's coming back here.

224
00:14:32.873 --> 00:14:34.875
I know. It's insane.

225
00:14:36.418 --> 00:14:37.586
You gotta do something.

226
00:14:38.711 --> 00:14:40.923
- What can I do?
- Oh. I don't know.

227
00:14:42.298 --> 00:14:45.885
Maybe take a cue
from the folks up on Mars.

228
00:14:47.471 --> 00:14:48.471
Push back.

229
00:14:54.227 --> 00:14:56.812
[Mars FIDO 1] Hopper 3<i>.</i> Phoenix.
<i>you're clear to disengage.</i>

230
00:14:56.812 --> 00:15:00.149
[Mars FIDO 2] <i>Clearing clean separation.
You are clear of docking zone.</i>

231
00:15:00.149 --> 00:15:03.320
<i>We have a good transponder mark
and you are clear to maneuver.</i>

232
00:15:04.278 --> 00:15:07.865
[Mars FIDO 1] <i>Happy Valley flight control
has your landing at beacon 1-5.</i>

233
00:15:07.865 --> 00:15:10.826
[pilot] Phoenix<i>.</i> Hopper 3
<i>reading you five by five.</i>

234
00:15:10.826 --> 00:15:15.164
<i>Board is green and we're on track
for nominal entry at 0217.</i>

235
00:15:15.874 --> 00:15:18.585
Zero down range. EDL surge on.

236
00:15:19.211 --> 00:15:21.296
Almost through the chop. folks.

237
00:15:22.630 --> 00:15:24.465
[Mars FIDO 1]
<i>You've got a good acceleration profile</i>

238
00:15:24.466 --> 00:15:26.552
<i>and excellent engine performance.</i>

239
00:15:30.681 --> 00:15:33.642
Squeeze my hand. You're doing so good.

240
00:15:35.476 --> 00:15:38.437
Hey. little man.
What you're feeling now is just turbulence

241
00:15:38.437 --> 00:15:41.482
as we enter Mars's atmosphere.
Same as on an airplane.

242
00:15:43.777 --> 00:15:46.111
[pilot] Looks like
we're through the rough patch.

243
00:15:46.113 --> 00:15:47.697
Smooth sailing from here on in.

244
00:15:48.365 --> 00:15:50.448
We'll be on the surface
in a few minutes. folks.

245
00:15:50.450 --> 00:15:51.994
You see that canyon down there?

246
00:15:53.245 --> 00:15:54.703
That's Valles Marineris.

247
00:15:54.705 --> 00:15:56.706
It is four times bigger
than the Grand Canyon.

248
00:15:56.706 --> 00:15:58.792
and our new home is at the bottom of it.

249
00:16:00.543 --> 00:16:04.047
[Mars FIDO 1] Hopper 3<i>. you're clear
for final approach on beacon 1-5.</i>

250
00:16:05.131 --> 00:16:08.634
[pilot] <i>Roger that.</i> Hopper 3 is clear
<i>for final approach on beacon 1-5.</i>

251
00:16:20.230 --> 00:16:21.605
Welcome to Happy Valley.

252
00:16:21.606 --> 00:16:24.275
- Danielle.
- [both chuckle]

253
00:16:27.321 --> 00:16:31.740
And you must be the young Luke Skywalker.

254
00:16:31.741 --> 00:16:33.283
[Alex] It's Alex. Mrs. Poole.

255
00:16:33.284 --> 00:16:36.163
[Danielle] Okay. [speaks indistinctly]

256
00:16:36.788 --> 00:16:38.748
And you may be our youngest crew member.

257
00:16:38.749 --> 00:16:41.918
but that doesn't mean
we don't have high expectations for you.

258
00:16:41.918 --> 00:16:45.004
[Danielle speaks indistinctly] ...grown so
much since the last time I saw you.

259
00:16:45.004 --> 00:16:46.088
[Palmer] Sir.

260
00:16:46.881 --> 00:16:47.881
Welcome.

261
00:16:47.883 --> 00:16:51.219
I cannot begin to tell you
how happy I am to have you here.

262
00:16:51.220 --> 00:16:54.596
I. uh. wish there was
a little bit more of a welcome.

263
00:16:54.597 --> 00:16:56.974
but. uh. with the strike...

264
00:16:56.975 --> 00:16:58.976
It's fine. I prefer it this way.

265
00:16:59.937 --> 00:17:03.648
- [Palmer] We haven't quite figured out...
- [Danielle] Give me a sec. Kel.

266
00:17:03.649 --> 00:17:06.192
...how to get everyone's stowed gear
off the transport.

267
00:17:06.192 --> 00:17:09.862
If you'd like to come with me. I can show
you your quarters. maybe give you a tour

268
00:17:09.863 --> 00:17:11.990
- around the facilities...
- Belay that. XO.

269
00:17:13.075 --> 00:17:16.285
You and me. we need to talk.
There have been some new developments.

270
00:17:16.286 --> 00:17:17.494
This way.

271
00:17:17.496 --> 00:17:18.578
[Palmer] Welcome.

272
00:17:19.079 --> 00:17:23.460
Palmer here will. uh. get you anything
you need and show you to your quarters.

273
00:17:24.670 --> 00:17:25.876
Welcome.

274
00:17:25.877 --> 00:17:27.337
Here. Let me get that for you.

275
00:17:27.338 --> 00:17:29.089
- Thank you.
- [strains] Here we go.

276
00:17:29.090 --> 00:17:31.134
All right. Follow me.

277
00:17:32.134 --> 00:17:34.095
Mommy. Where's Poppy?

278
00:17:34.096 --> 00:17:35.846
Oh. I'm sure
he just got a little delayed...

279
00:17:35.847 --> 00:17:37.140
[Ed] Kel!

280
00:17:38.141 --> 00:17:39.142
- [chuckles]
- Dad.

281
00:17:42.019 --> 00:17:43.020
Hey.

282
00:17:43.855 --> 00:17:44.856
[Ed sighs]

283
00:17:46.650 --> 00:17:47.984
Sorry. I'm a little late.

284
00:17:50.194 --> 00:17:52.239
There's my grandson.

285
00:17:54.240 --> 00:17:56.826
- Alex. it's Poppy.
- [Ed] Hey.

286
00:17:57.994 --> 00:17:59.453
You wanna give Poppy a hug. kiddo?

287
00:18:00.747 --> 00:18:01.999
No?

288
00:18:03.666 --> 00:18:06.586
He gets like this sometimes.
Probably just a little overwhelmed.

289
00:18:06.586 --> 00:18:08.337
Yeah. well. that makes sense.

290
00:18:10.257 --> 00:18:11.758
That's okay. buddy.

291
00:18:12.634 --> 00:18:13.675
[Ed. Kelly chuckle]

292
00:18:13.676 --> 00:18:15.635
Come on. you two.
Let's get you settled then.

293
00:18:15.636 --> 00:18:16.721
Okay.

294
00:18:20.224 --> 00:18:22.728
- [Ed] Ah. Palmer. Finally useful.
- [Kelly chuckles]

295
00:18:25.939 --> 00:18:27.356
[Dev] That's quite the view.

296
00:18:28.858 --> 00:18:32.988
Look. I know
this is all new and exciting for you.

297
00:18:33.739 --> 00:18:36.699
but right now we're working on a way
to get over to the cryo center.

298
00:18:36.700 --> 00:18:38.951
We've got a crisis on our hands.

299
00:18:38.951 --> 00:18:41.872
And it's not just a NASA problem
or an M-7 problem.

300
00:18:42.580 --> 00:18:44.080
These are your workers.

301
00:18:44.082 --> 00:18:47.335
They've got legitimate grievances
against your company.

302
00:18:47.336 --> 00:18:49.587
So I'd like to know
how you plan to proceed.

303
00:18:51.006 --> 00:18:53.049
I am considering my options.

304
00:18:53.842 --> 00:18:55.969
You've had plenty of time
to consider your options.

305
00:18:56.595 --> 00:18:58.637
We gotta get this thing resolved now.

306
00:18:58.638 --> 00:19:00.891
Or that asteroid becomes a distant memory.

307
00:19:01.391 --> 00:19:04.185
Thank you for showing me to my quarters.
Commander Poole.

308
00:19:04.894 --> 00:19:05.895
Much appreciated.

309
00:19:08.648 --> 00:19:09.650
[Danielle sighs]

310
00:19:17.990 --> 00:19:21.369
Dev. I know
you're used to being in charge.

311
00:19:22.037 --> 00:19:24.248
but when you're up here on my base.

312
00:19:25.207 --> 00:19:27.625
what I say goes. Clear?

313
00:19:28.876 --> 00:19:29.877
Crystal.

314
00:19:37.927 --> 00:19:39.512
- [Dimitri] In.
- [Alex inhales]

315
00:19:40.806 --> 00:19:43.223
- Out.
- [exhales]

316
00:19:43.224 --> 00:19:45.394
Good. Now other side.

317
00:19:47.895 --> 00:19:48.896
Mm-hmm.

318
00:19:50.356 --> 00:19:52.483
Mm-hmm. Good.

319
00:19:53.359 --> 00:19:54.736
I'd like to run some blood work.

320
00:19:56.238 --> 00:19:57.573
Don't worry. Not today.

321
00:19:59.575 --> 00:20:03.494
Did you know I worked with your father
for two and a half years?

322
00:20:04.078 --> 00:20:05.204
Even right here.

323
00:20:06.123 --> 00:20:07.207
Did you like him?

324
00:20:08.083 --> 00:20:09.375
I liked him very much.

325
00:20:10.085 --> 00:20:11.461
He loved playing games.

326
00:20:12.546 --> 00:20:13.963
and he would always beat me.

327
00:20:14.714 --> 00:20:19.218
He would find anything around.
nuts. bolts. candy for the queen.

328
00:20:19.219 --> 00:20:20.971
and use them as chess pieces.

329
00:20:21.888 --> 00:20:22.888
I know chess.

330
00:20:22.890 --> 00:20:25.223
I thought you might.

331
00:20:25.224 --> 00:20:27.227
Maybe we could play? [chuckles]

332
00:20:27.853 --> 00:20:29.436
He's doing quite well.

333
00:20:29.438 --> 00:20:30.730
Low gravity suits him.

334
00:20:30.730 --> 00:20:32.940
Comparing his charts from Houston.

335
00:20:32.941 --> 00:20:35.986
both his blood pressure and respiration
are actually stronger.

336
00:20:36.569 --> 00:20:38.447
He's more at home here than on Earth.

337
00:20:39.573 --> 00:20:40.574
Thank you. Dima.

338
00:20:41.157 --> 00:20:42.409
So good to see you again.

339
00:20:43.660 --> 00:20:44.661
Both of you.

340
00:20:45.244 --> 00:20:46.244
You too.

341
00:20:46.246 --> 00:20:50.334
[astronauts. cosmonauts grunting]

342
00:20:51.919 --> 00:20:53.753
[Palmer] Keep moving. Stay together.

343
00:20:56.548 --> 00:20:59.968
[astronaut 1] Christ. This feels like
the longest 800 meters on Mars.

344
00:21:00.635 --> 00:21:04.596
[Palmer] If you'd rather walk out there
without a suit on. be my guest.

345
00:21:04.597 --> 00:21:09.018
[astronaut 2] It's okay. Jennings.
You get scared. I'll hold your hand.

346
00:21:09.019 --> 00:21:10.310
Fuck off. Bishop.

347
00:21:10.311 --> 00:21:12.396
[Palmer] Quit yakking and keep moving.

348
00:21:36.712 --> 00:21:40.215
[devices beeping]

349
00:21:40.217 --> 00:21:44.636
Ops-Com. Entry Team 1. we have
reached the main fuel generator control.

350
00:21:44.637 --> 00:21:46.055
Good.

351
00:21:46.056 --> 00:21:47.140
Mr. Howard.

352
00:21:49.351 --> 00:21:52.854
Run a systems check and
have them bring everything back up online.

353
00:21:52.855 --> 00:21:54.646
Entry Team 1. Ops-Com.

354
00:21:54.647 --> 00:21:58.192
you are good to proceed
with reactivation of argon liquefaction

355
00:21:58.192 --> 00:22:00.027
<i>and methane generation.</i>

356
00:22:00.028 --> 00:22:04.365
Time to start making some of that sweet.
sweet galactic go-juice.

357
00:22:04.365 --> 00:22:06.451
[jazz music playing]

358
00:22:07.994 --> 00:22:08.996
How is it?

359
00:22:10.038 --> 00:22:11.247
- Good.
- Yeah?

360
00:22:11.248 --> 00:22:12.332
Real good.

361
00:22:13.500 --> 00:22:17.171
I don't know. I feel like it's. um.
it's missing something.

362
00:22:17.880 --> 00:22:18.922
Yeah.

363
00:22:19.589 --> 00:22:22.300
Can't quite put my finger on it.

364
00:22:26.512 --> 00:22:28.515
[both laugh]

365
00:22:29.348 --> 00:22:31.226
[Ed] Oh. wow.

366
00:22:32.644 --> 00:22:34.770
Oh. you done good. kiddo.

367
00:22:36.105 --> 00:22:37.523
[laughs]

368
00:22:38.442 --> 00:22:40.527
- Oh. yeah.
- [laughs]

369
00:22:41.694 --> 00:22:42.862
Oh. yeah.

370
00:22:42.863 --> 00:22:44.989
- You want some of this. buddy?
- No. thank you.

371
00:22:44.990 --> 00:22:47.700
[Ed] Oh. It's the best.
You're gonna love it. You gotta try this.

372
00:22:47.701 --> 00:22:50.286
Oh. there you go. Yeah.

373
00:22:50.287 --> 00:22:51.913
Now mix it up.

374
00:22:52.497 --> 00:22:53.707
You gotta mix it.

375
00:23:01.673 --> 00:23:02.965
Why'd you do that?

376
00:23:03.967 --> 00:23:04.967
It was cheese.

377
00:23:04.968 --> 00:23:06.053
[Kelly sighs]

378
00:23:06.845 --> 00:23:10.388
I'm trying to broaden his horizons
a little bit.

379
00:23:10.390 --> 00:23:11.891
Well. maybe before you do that.

380
00:23:11.892 --> 00:23:14.059
you can actually try to get to know him
a little bit.

381
00:23:14.060 --> 00:23:15.895
instead of playing Norma Rae.

382
00:23:16.646 --> 00:23:19.523
- I'm trying here. Okay?
- Are you?

383
00:23:19.525 --> 00:23:23.694
[stammers] Cut me some slack here. kiddo.
I'm-I'm-I'm fighting for something here.

384
00:23:24.278 --> 00:23:25.613
I'm Helios too.

385
00:23:25.614 --> 00:23:28.657
So come fight with us.

386
00:23:28.659 --> 00:23:29.742
With me.

387
00:23:32.828 --> 00:23:36.499
You're being so myopic.
There's more than one way to see this.

388
00:23:36.500 --> 00:23:40.336
Aleida Rosales.
she worked a miracle in Leningrad.

389
00:23:40.336 --> 00:23:43.965
Okay. She came up with something
that will change our planet forever.

390
00:23:44.549 --> 00:23:47.634
Yeah. And it'll end everything
we worked for on this one.

391
00:23:47.635 --> 00:23:50.179
There will still be
a robust research presence here.

392
00:23:50.180 --> 00:23:53.391
They're not just gonna fold up
and go home.

393
00:23:53.392 --> 00:23:55.852
That's my point exactly.

394
00:23:55.853 --> 00:23:59.188
It'll end up being
some scientific backwater like McMurdo.

395
00:23:59.189 --> 00:24:00.856
What's wrong with McMurdo?

396
00:24:00.857 --> 00:24:03.526
Nothing. But this place could just be
so much more

397
00:24:03.527 --> 00:24:06.278
than 10 white-coats and a cleaning lady.

398
00:24:06.279 --> 00:24:07.905
It can be a real colony.

399
00:24:09.115 --> 00:24:10.116
A home.

400
00:24:11.410 --> 00:24:13.911
- You already have a home.
- [scoffs]

401
00:24:13.912 --> 00:24:15.122
[knocking on door]

402
00:24:16.832 --> 00:24:17.833
[grunts]

403
00:24:22.336 --> 00:24:24.964
- Huh?
- Skipper. we got a problem.

404
00:24:26.549 --> 00:24:28.843
[clamoring]

405
00:24:28.844 --> 00:24:30.721
[worker] Fuck. We get nothing.

406
00:24:36.351 --> 00:24:37.768
Why is it that you're the only one

407
00:24:37.769 --> 00:24:39.394
- who doesn't get it?
- All right.

408
00:24:39.395 --> 00:24:40.938
[clamoring ends]

409
00:24:40.939 --> 00:24:44.734
Well. we are fucked now. man.
All our leverage is in that fuel plant.

410
00:24:45.484 --> 00:24:47.362
- How'd they get to it?
- We don't know.

411
00:24:48.029 --> 00:24:51.866
Well. they'll have a tough time starting
those gennies back up without this guy.

412
00:24:55.453 --> 00:24:57.288
[Ed] The primary gas flow regulator?

413
00:24:58.289 --> 00:25:00.750
Grabbed it when we were clearing out
just in case.

414
00:25:01.710 --> 00:25:04.586
[astronaut] All right.
the voltage limiter is back online.

415
00:25:04.587 --> 00:25:07.508
- [Palmer] Copy that. Here we go.
- [machinery revs]

416
00:25:08.299 --> 00:25:12.720
No joy. The intake pipes don't seem
to be flowing atmo into the chamber.

417
00:25:12.721 --> 00:25:14.181
All right. Hold.

418
00:25:14.806 --> 00:25:17.099
Jennings. check the condenser.

419
00:25:23.065 --> 00:25:25.150
[pipe rattling]

420
00:25:25.901 --> 00:25:26.902
Take a look.

421
00:25:31.405 --> 00:25:33.659
They took out
the primary gas flow regulator.

422
00:25:34.159 --> 00:25:36.869
I'm gonna try rerouting the flow
through the secondary.

423
00:25:38.247 --> 00:25:40.830
You can't just bypass a regulator.

424
00:25:40.832 --> 00:25:44.794
Relax. Where I grew up.
missing parts were all in a day's work.

425
00:25:44.795 --> 00:25:46.797
All we did was find work-arounds.

426
00:25:48.048 --> 00:25:49.799
[tools clinking]

427
00:25:51.969 --> 00:25:53.220
[beeping]

428
00:26:03.313 --> 00:26:05.315
[gas hissing]

429
00:26:14.199 --> 00:26:15.282
[device beeping]

430
00:26:15.284 --> 00:26:18.618
- [hissing continues. lock clicks]
- Okay. Try now.

431
00:26:18.619 --> 00:26:20.788
[typing]

432
00:26:22.457 --> 00:26:23.458
[beeps]

433
00:26:24.750 --> 00:26:26.335
[machinery revving]

434
00:26:26.336 --> 00:26:28.838
[Palmer chuckles]

435
00:26:30.214 --> 00:26:31.299
Bingo party.

436
00:26:31.842 --> 00:26:35.429
[Danielle. on radio] <i>Beautiful. The
argon generators are coming back online.</i>

437
00:26:37.055 --> 00:26:39.641
[machinery rattles]

438
00:26:43.060 --> 00:26:46.355
[controller] Commander. some of
these readings are starting to tip red.

439
00:26:48.275 --> 00:26:50.442
- What the hell?
- [machinery rumbles]

440
00:26:50.443 --> 00:26:52.487
[beeping]

441
00:26:54.530 --> 00:26:56.200
[siren blaring]

442
00:26:57.159 --> 00:26:59.660
Shut it down. Tell him to shut it down.

443
00:26:59.661 --> 00:27:02.705
- Hit the emergency cut-off breaker!
- [rumbling continues]

444
00:27:22.267 --> 00:27:26.438
Ms. Rosales. did we have a meeting
scheduled with Administrator Hobson?

445
00:27:27.146 --> 00:27:28.147
We need to talk.

446
00:27:30.483 --> 00:27:31.484
Um.

447
00:27:32.318 --> 00:27:35.238
All right. Uh. let me just sign this.
I'll tell you. at NASA. the...

448
00:27:35.239 --> 00:27:37.448
Do not give Margo Madison
diplomatic immunity.

449
00:27:37.449 --> 00:27:39.450
- Just jumping right in. Okay.
- You need to call

450
00:27:39.451 --> 00:27:42.662
the Department of Defense or the
White House or whoever you have to call.

451
00:27:42.663 --> 00:27:44.704
- whatever you have to do. Just do it.
- It's not up to me.

452
00:27:44.705 --> 00:27:45.874
Do not let her come here.

453
00:27:47.166 --> 00:27:49.211
Not to Houston. not to this building.

454
00:27:50.253 --> 00:27:54.423
If she steps foot on American soil.
she should be arrested. and you know it.

455
00:27:54.423 --> 00:27:57.551
I understand your anger.
but Moscow is insisting

456
00:27:57.552 --> 00:28:01.513
Margo co-chair these working sessions
on engine fabrication.

457
00:28:01.515 --> 00:28:05.227
attachment. slingshot
and earthbound escort.

458
00:28:06.269 --> 00:28:08.436
You know.
they're just doing this to embarrass us.

459
00:28:08.438 --> 00:28:11.107
Probably. but my hands
are tied here. Aleida.

460
00:28:11.607 --> 00:28:14.861
- According to the M-7 charter...
- Oh. fuck the M-7 charter.

461
00:28:14.862 --> 00:28:18.365
How would they like it if we had
Arkady Shevchenko representing Helios?

462
00:28:19.240 --> 00:28:21.576
Might as well
if this is gonna be a big pissing match.

463
00:28:23.287 --> 00:28:25.038
Aleida. I hear you. I do.

464
00:28:25.663 --> 00:28:29.917
But the fact remains she is the head
of their asteroid capture program.

465
00:28:30.460 --> 00:28:33.172
and an incredibly skilled engineer
to boot.

466
00:28:33.963 --> 00:28:38.009
If we're gonna pull this off. we need
the best people from all over the world.

467
00:28:40.761 --> 00:28:42.680
- Well. I can't work with her.
- [door opens]

468
00:28:42.681 --> 00:28:44.441
- Well. before you start...
- [employee] Sir.

469
00:28:45.601 --> 00:28:48.561
There's been an accident at Happy Valley.

470
00:28:53.650 --> 00:28:56.903
[aide] Doctor. we have multiple wounded
patients coming in from the explosion.

471
00:28:56.903 --> 00:28:58.403
[Dimitri] I need an IV.

472
00:28:58.404 --> 00:29:00.489
- [people clamoring]
- Stabilize him.

473
00:29:00.490 --> 00:29:03.868
Burns are full thickness.
Muscles are in contracture.

474
00:29:04.619 --> 00:29:08.288
You! Arterial line kit in that cabinet.
Come on! [speaks Russian]

475
00:29:08.289 --> 00:29:10.000
[in English] Doc! Last one.

476
00:29:10.584 --> 00:29:12.169
[Dimitri] Push left over here.

477
00:29:12.752 --> 00:29:15.671
Keep an eye on Jennings.
Vitals are starting to stabilize.

478
00:29:15.672 --> 00:29:18.925
We need to protect her airway.
Get her on O2.

479
00:29:19.926 --> 00:29:21.595
Third degree. but we can debride.

480
00:29:22.429 --> 00:29:23.555
Start an IV.

481
00:29:24.096 --> 00:29:26.223
Need three liters lactated Ringer's.

482
00:29:26.224 --> 00:29:27.726
Cover those wounds in gauze.

483
00:29:28.519 --> 00:29:29.936
[rhythmic beeping]

484
00:29:32.021 --> 00:29:34.190
- [aide] Doctor. he's bradying down.
- [steady beep]

485
00:29:34.191 --> 00:29:35.357
- Jennings?
- Get a line in.

486
00:29:35.358 --> 00:29:37.652
[aide] Coming through. Move it. Move it.

487
00:29:37.653 --> 00:29:39.194
[steady beep continues]

488
00:29:39.195 --> 00:29:40.572
[clamoring continues]

489
00:29:44.367 --> 00:29:45.368
Mike.

490
00:29:46.286 --> 00:29:47.871
How many casualties?

491
00:29:48.579 --> 00:29:50.163
We have one fatality so far.

492
00:29:50.164 --> 00:29:51.457
Four more badly injured.

493
00:29:51.458 --> 00:29:53.542
Two in critical condition.

494
00:29:53.544 --> 00:29:56.878
Dima is doing his best to keep them alive.
but it's... it's not looking good.

495
00:29:56.880 --> 00:29:58.339
Oh. goddamn it.

496
00:30:00.008 --> 00:30:02.969
They have dramatically escalated things
up there. Eli.

497
00:30:02.970 --> 00:30:04.679
And we need to respond.

498
00:30:04.680 --> 00:30:06.931
What we need to do is get Poole some help.

499
00:30:06.932 --> 00:30:09.558
I agree.
Things are getting out of control.

500
00:30:09.559 --> 00:30:12.644
Sir. Central Intelligence knows for a fact

501
00:30:12.645 --> 00:30:15.982
that Moscow has at least
one KGB asset in Happy Valley.

502
00:30:16.567 --> 00:30:17.567
Of course they do.

503
00:30:17.567 --> 00:30:19.693
You're not saying they were involved?

504
00:30:19.694 --> 00:30:21.113
No. We don't believe so.

505
00:30:21.779 --> 00:30:24.990
The thing is there are options
at NASA's disposal

506
00:30:24.991 --> 00:30:27.618
to get things under control
that you may not be aware of.

507
00:30:30.038 --> 00:30:32.582
Are you saying
we have assets up there too?

508
00:30:32.583 --> 00:30:35.419
- We do.
- How are we just now hearing about this?

509
00:30:36.044 --> 00:30:40.088
There are 12 North Koreans sitting
a couple hundred feet from Ops-Com.

510
00:30:40.089 --> 00:30:41.715
Uh... Can you blame us?

511
00:30:41.717 --> 00:30:44.551
Are there any weapons on the base
I should know about?

512
00:30:44.552 --> 00:30:49.015
Our man has access to standard attenuated
energy projectile systems.

513
00:30:49.016 --> 00:30:52.476
high pressure. nitrogen weapons.
firing non lethal rounds

514
00:30:52.477 --> 00:30:54.895
and they can't pierce
the walls of the habs.

515
00:30:54.896 --> 00:30:57.481
- And skin?
- It doesn't tickle.

516
00:30:57.982 --> 00:30:59.401
Delightful.

517
00:31:00.736 --> 00:31:02.112
So you're suggesting what?

518
00:31:02.988 --> 00:31:06.615
That we have the CIA
and the KGB take control of the base?

519
00:31:06.616 --> 00:31:11.203
We just thought you should know.
I... In case things did escalate.

520
00:31:11.204 --> 00:31:12.496
Oh. I hear you. Bob.

521
00:31:12.497 --> 00:31:13.998
But I am not gonna be the guy

522
00:31:13.999 --> 00:31:18.336
that authorizes the CIA
to implement martial law on Mars.

523
00:31:18.336 --> 00:31:21.923
We need to reestablish
firm control of this base

524
00:31:21.923 --> 00:31:23.715
and stop these terrorist attacks
from happening.

525
00:31:23.717 --> 00:31:25.550
Terrorism? Really?

526
00:31:25.551 --> 00:31:27.345
Well. what would you call it. Eli?

527
00:31:27.346 --> 00:31:28.721
I mean. it's happened before.

528
00:31:28.721 --> 00:31:30.890
- In fact. it's happened right here.
- Enough.

529
00:31:30.891 --> 00:31:32.351
End of conversation.

530
00:31:33.894 --> 00:31:36.188
We need to find another solution here.

531
00:31:38.648 --> 00:31:42.234
Uh. maybe... maybe we send up
a security detail like in '83.

532
00:31:42.236 --> 00:31:44.654
[chuckles]
Yeah. because that went so well.

533
00:31:45.239 --> 00:31:46.614
They stopped World War III.

534
00:31:46.615 --> 00:31:49.116
Well. you could argue
that it almost caused it.

535
00:31:50.911 --> 00:31:51.911
[sighs]

536
00:31:51.912 --> 00:31:53.663
We don't have enough time anyway.

537
00:31:54.623 --> 00:31:57.166
Between training and travel.
it would take months.

538
00:31:58.836 --> 00:32:00.711
Unless we didn't need to send them up.

539
00:32:02.463 --> 00:32:07.885
We could deputize people on Happy Valley.
people with adequate military training.

540
00:32:09.846 --> 00:32:12.516
Well. how many people are there
like that up there?

541
00:32:13.307 --> 00:32:17.229
Between us and the Soviets. uh.
it must be at least a dozen. if not more.

542
00:32:20.022 --> 00:32:21.023
All right...

543
00:32:23.109 --> 00:32:24.361
let's do that.

544
00:32:25.112 --> 00:32:27.696
[Danielle]
This isn't why any of us came up here.

545
00:32:27.698 --> 00:32:31.910
but it's our duty now
to ensure the security of this base

546
00:32:32.493 --> 00:32:33.996
and the safety of this crew.

547
00:32:34.663 --> 00:32:37.623
<i>We need to find those responsible
for this explosion.</i>

548
00:32:37.624 --> 00:32:40.917
<i>So keep your eyes open
for anything suspect.</i>

549
00:32:40.919 --> 00:32:45.548
<i>We have got to make certain that
a tragedy like this never happens again.</i>

550
00:32:45.548 --> 00:32:47.549
[resident 1] Shit. man. Put my stuff down!

551
00:32:47.550 --> 00:32:49.552
[people arguing. clamoring]

552
00:32:54.432 --> 00:32:56.601
[resident 2] Hey. Watch it.
That's personal property.

553
00:32:56.602 --> 00:32:58.728
- Hey. stop touching my... [grunts]
- Back off!

554
00:32:58.729 --> 00:33:01.480
What are... What the fuck?
Get your hands off him.

555
00:33:01.480 --> 00:33:04.482
[Helios employees shouting. clamoring]

556
00:33:04.483 --> 00:33:06.986
Nothing changes. We keep the pressure on.

557
00:33:06.987 --> 00:33:09.029
The pressure? Jennings is dead.

558
00:33:09.030 --> 00:33:10.781
This has gone too far.

559
00:33:14.786 --> 00:33:18.332
Listen up! Listen up!

560
00:33:28.634 --> 00:33:31.678
You guys negotiated with clarity
and with force.

561
00:33:33.012 --> 00:33:34.138
I respect that.

562
00:33:36.349 --> 00:33:37.433
And you stood your ground.

563
00:33:39.560 --> 00:33:43.315
I respect that... even more.

564
00:33:44.148 --> 00:33:48.903
But the truth is
unless we resolve this today. right now.

565
00:33:48.903 --> 00:33:51.614
and get that fuel plant repaired
and pumping liquid argon

566
00:33:51.615 --> 00:33:55.410
so we can capture the most valuable
known object in our solar system.

567
00:33:56.036 --> 00:33:57.286
then we've failed.

568
00:33:57.287 --> 00:33:58.371
All of us.

569
00:33:58.372 --> 00:34:00.664
Okay. so. then give us
what we're asking for.

570
00:34:00.665 --> 00:34:03.584
- [Helios employees] Yeah. Yeah.
- Send Goldilocks to Mars.

571
00:34:03.585 --> 00:34:06.672
Look. I wish I could tell you
that were a possibility. but the truth is

572
00:34:07.463 --> 00:34:11.925
the nations of Earth will never.
never send this asteroid to Mars.

573
00:34:11.927 --> 00:34:13.135
You know why?

574
00:34:13.846 --> 00:34:15.972
Because it's not
in their financial interest

575
00:34:15.972 --> 00:34:17.891
and space is a business.

576
00:34:18.474 --> 00:34:19.599
It's about resources.

577
00:34:19.601 --> 00:34:21.518
It's about the bottom line.
It's about profit.

578
00:34:21.519 --> 00:34:22.644
[worker 1] Fuck your profit!

579
00:34:22.646 --> 00:34:25.188
[Dev] You know. go ahead
and scoff all you want to.

580
00:34:25.190 --> 00:34:27.775
but I mean. that's what this strike
is all about. isn't it?

581
00:34:28.735 --> 00:34:32.572
- You want your cut. your slice of the pie.
- [worker 2] Damn right! I want my cut!

582
00:34:33.072 --> 00:34:36.659
You came here to make a living.

583
00:34:37.452 --> 00:34:42.123
But what you're asking.
changing the destination of this asteroid.

584
00:34:42.666 --> 00:34:46.003
that is never going to happen.

585
00:34:46.878 --> 00:34:48.795
But I'm gonna tell you what can happen.

586
00:34:48.797 --> 00:34:53.217
NASA and Roscosmos have agreed
to your workplace safety concerns.

587
00:34:54.344 --> 00:34:55.969
And as CEO of Helios.

588
00:34:55.971 --> 00:35:00.391
I'm ready to offer you a 40% increase
in your pension contributions...

589
00:35:00.391 --> 00:35:02.143
[scattered applause]

590
00:35:02.143 --> 00:35:07.773
...a more generous health plan
and shares of Helios stock to everybody.

591
00:35:07.773 --> 00:35:11.985
Don't believe a goddamn word
this man says. he's a snake oil salesman.

592
00:35:11.987 --> 00:35:14.030
I'll also make sure
that everybody involved in this strike

593
00:35:14.030 --> 00:35:15.989
gets amnesty for any and all actions

594
00:35:15.990 --> 00:35:18.867
conducted during the negotiations
of the last few days.

595
00:35:18.869 --> 00:35:24.748
And the first 100 people to cross this
line will receive a quadruple payday bonus

596
00:35:24.750 --> 00:35:30.130
which will put you just north of
a million dollars each.

597
00:35:30.630 --> 00:35:32.547
[Helios employees murmuring]

598
00:35:32.548 --> 00:35:34.342
Don't listen to him.

599
00:35:35.927 --> 00:35:37.804
Can't you see what he's trying to do?

600
00:35:38.472 --> 00:35:42.141
He's trying to buy us off
and undercut our solidarity.

601
00:35:42.141 --> 00:35:44.936
We can still win this
if we stick together.

602
00:35:44.936 --> 00:35:46.311
That's right.

603
00:35:46.313 --> 00:35:48.688
[Dev] Okay. yeah. Sure.
You can try to do that.

604
00:35:48.690 --> 00:35:51.817
But you have to ask yourself.
"What's more important?"

605
00:35:51.818 --> 00:35:57.074
Some abstract notion of togetherness.
or is it your families back home?

606
00:35:57.740 --> 00:36:00.826
Is it your kids. your... your nieces.
your nephews.

607
00:36:00.827 --> 00:36:04.081
your parents. your grandparents.

608
00:36:04.789 --> 00:36:10.001
or is it some rock
that is floating out in space?

609
00:36:10.003 --> 00:36:12.255
[Helios employees murmuring]

610
00:36:15.467 --> 00:36:16.925
Sorry. Sam.

611
00:36:16.927 --> 00:36:18.052
Henry?

612
00:36:19.679 --> 00:36:21.014
[scoffs]

613
00:36:23.432 --> 00:36:25.518
I rep 12 at the fuel plant.

614
00:36:25.518 --> 00:36:27.269
- Welcome.
- Thank you.

615
00:36:27.271 --> 00:36:28.480
I've got 88 more.

616
00:36:29.063 --> 00:36:30.065
Come on!

617
00:36:31.108 --> 00:36:33.610
- Hey. hey. Don't do this. Don't do this.
- What are you doing?

618
00:36:36.070 --> 00:36:38.907
Cowards. Quitters.

619
00:36:40.909 --> 00:36:42.286
Must stand strong.

620
00:36:46.706 --> 00:36:47.875
Y'all make me sick.

621
00:36:53.797 --> 00:36:54.797
Ilya?

622
00:36:57.175 --> 00:36:58.510
Maya?

623
00:36:59.552 --> 00:37:01.929
Immunity. Skip. Sorry.

624
00:37:10.355 --> 00:37:12.900
I rep all 18 in fab. weld and finish.

625
00:37:24.077 --> 00:37:26.204
Luka. Luka!

626
00:37:36.590 --> 00:37:37.798
Well done. Dev.

627
00:37:39.050 --> 00:37:40.719
You just killed Mars.

628
00:37:47.518 --> 00:37:50.478
[news reporter] <i>... and former director
of NASA. Margo Madison.</i>

629
00:37:50.478 --> 00:37:52.646
<i>has returned to the United States</i>

630
00:37:52.648 --> 00:37:56.108
<i>nearly a decade
after defecting to the Soviet Union.</i>

631
00:37:56.108 --> 00:38:00.237
<i>Her arrival in Houston today
was met with massive protests.</i>

632
00:38:00.239 --> 00:38:05.826
<i>Many calling for her arrest though Madison
is protected by a diplomatic immunity</i>

633
00:38:05.827 --> 00:38:09.373
<i>while she is here in her role
as the head of Roscosmos as...</i>

634
00:38:12.166 --> 00:38:14.378
[sirens blaring]

635
00:38:16.380 --> 00:38:19.215
[reporters chattering]

636
00:38:24.972 --> 00:38:27.807
- [sirens blaring]
- [camera shutters clicking]

637
00:38:39.610 --> 00:38:41.487
[sighs]

638
00:38:41.989 --> 00:38:44.740
- [reporters chattering]
- [camera shutters clicking]

639
00:38:53.166 --> 00:38:55.960
Margo Madison. I'm Eli Hobson.

640
00:38:56.670 --> 00:38:58.380
Welcome to the Molly Cobb Space Center.

641
00:38:59.297 --> 00:39:00.465
Thank you.

642
00:39:01.757 --> 00:39:02.759
Shall we?

643
00:39:33.164 --> 00:39:36.751
- [bicycle pedaling]
- [panting]

644
00:39:41.590 --> 00:39:43.342
- [knocking on door]
- [door opens]

645
00:39:45.219 --> 00:39:46.302
Admiral.

646
00:39:46.302 --> 00:39:47.929
- What the hell?
- [door closes]

647
00:39:50.014 --> 00:39:52.891
[sighs] You got some nerve
coming in here after what you just did.

648
00:39:52.893 --> 00:39:57.480
Admittedly so. but. uh. I need your help.

649
00:39:57.481 --> 00:39:59.231
Why the fuck would I help you?

650
00:39:59.233 --> 00:40:02.235
Because we both want the same thing...
To never go back.

651
00:40:02.235 --> 00:40:04.445
You don't know... [scoffs]

652
00:40:04.445 --> 00:40:07.407
You're still here. aren't you?
After all these years?

653
00:40:08.282 --> 00:40:10.367
You and I both know
that Mars has the potential

654
00:40:10.369 --> 00:40:13.329
to become a living. breathing society.

655
00:40:13.329 --> 00:40:16.083
Something that lasts
well beyond the two of us...

656
00:40:17.458 --> 00:40:18.668
and we can make that happen.

657
00:40:19.378 --> 00:40:21.628
[scoffs] You just ruined
any chance of that.

658
00:40:21.630 --> 00:40:23.463
I know that was painful.

659
00:40:23.465 --> 00:40:24.882
Believe me. I know.

660
00:40:24.882 --> 00:40:29.554
To see how driven they all were
by self-interest. by greed.

661
00:40:30.179 --> 00:40:32.139
It would be funny
if it wasn't so predictable.

662
00:40:33.182 --> 00:40:36.226
But the strike.
for all its inconveniences.

663
00:40:36.228 --> 00:40:39.938
it wound up being a blessing.
because a few of you.

664
00:40:39.940 --> 00:40:42.442
you showed just how much
you believe in your cause.

665
00:40:43.402 --> 00:40:47.280
how much that you would sacrifice
for something greater than yourselves.

666
00:40:47.780 --> 00:40:51.826
And we're gonna need
as much of that as we can get.

667
00:40:51.827 --> 00:40:53.869
What the fuck are you talking about?

668
00:40:53.871 --> 00:40:59.876
I'm talking about the future. Ed.
About taking what is rightfully ours.

669
00:41:11.221 --> 00:41:12.764
You can't be serious.

670
00:41:14.141 --> 00:41:16.518
Do you want to help me steal an asteroid?

671
00:41:17.305 --> 00:42:17.677
